        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The current Neovim LSP experience is quite poor compared to coc.nvim. The configuration is scattered across different plugins and different places, and you have to piece them together manually. While some might consider this is \"decentralized\", I believe the basic, core LSP functionalities should be centralized in one place, or even built-in. Or at least a recommend config should be given out to contain all the features. Now there is just no such recommanded config. People just spend tons of time reading blogs, ask chatgpts, readiing plugin readmes.\r\n\r\nLSP is a complex and highly coupled  thing, it will consume the users too much time improve the default behaviour.",
