        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> doesn't automatically close the quicklist after hit enter\r\n\r\nWhy do you assume everyone wants this?\r\n\r\nThe rest of this issue is based on unfounded assumptions from the perspective that the builtin quickfix interface isn't good. It's actually very usable when paired with https://github.com/tpope/vim-unimpaired (which has some mappings we should include in Nvim by default).\r\n\r\nStarting with the assumption that the UI needs to match coc.nvim or vscode is a fallacy. There are many parts of vim such as quickfix which have tons of features, but require some investment. That is the general theme of vim in general, and if you don't think it's useful then there is no point in using vim. (Note that this is 100% orthogonal to monotonic improvements, i.e. improvements that can be made to Nvim defaults or features without throwing away the useful parts)",
