        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk please be aware that there are other issues even if you pointed that maybe the others don't want to automatically close:\r\n\r\n> no preview window, no highlight\r\n\r\nI don't think this issue should be closed. I didn't assume it should match with vscode or coc.nvim but it's just tooooo bad experience.\r\n\r\nEven if you ask GPT, it will still tell you that the user experience of coc.nvim is better than the current Neovim LSP, and it's more ready-to-use out of the box. Why don't learn from them on this part?",
