            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> no preview window, no highlight\r\n\r\nwhat is meant by \"no highlight\"? there is various kinds of highlighting. If you meant syntax highlighting in the quickfix , that isn't specific to LSP. There are existing issues tracking improvements to quickfix: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/15950\r\n\r\nOTOH, syntax highlight in quickfix could be a performance cost, so that would need to be weighed. Meanwhile, it's easy to install plugins that do this...\r\n\r\n> no preview window\r\n\r\nwe have existing issues tracking enhanced \"preview\" functionality: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/9920\r\n\r\nthat kind of generalized functionality is required, we aren't going to make non-trivial ad-hoc changes to LSP \"find references\".\r\n\r\n> Even if you ask GPT, it will still tell you that the user experience of coc.nvim is better than the current Neovim LSP\r\n\r\nGPT gets its opinions from the internet. wtf is that supposed to prove?",
