            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> what is meant by \"no highlight\"? \r\n\r\nno highlight/cursorline on the main window, syntax highlight is not important, but we should be able to match quickfix's current line with the main window. Now it's difficult to see which line it maps to\r\n\r\nit's also ok to not have preview window, as long as the mapping works then it should be ok.\r\n\r\n\r\n> why am I saying it's too bad?\r\nbecause if you cnext in quicklist window, because there is no preview window, no mapping, it has to jump to that pos of that file...people easily get lost. ESC cannot make sure the user is on the original file anymore. This is extremely bad!\r\n\r\n",
